Blobs are immutable in JS, so if you have a stream you end up having to buffer all the data in memory.

Here is a sample snippet

```js
async function readableStreamToBlob(readableStream, mimeType = "application/octet-stream") {
    const reader = readableStream.getReader();
    const chunks = [];

    while (true) {
        const { done, value } = await reader.read();
        if (done) break;
        chunks.push(value); // Buffering chunks in memory
    }

    return new Blob(chunks, { type: mimeType });
}

